Real Madrid have confirmed that Forward Takefusa Kubo on Thursday left the club to join RCD Mallorca on a season-long loan. The La Liga giants made this known in a statement on the club’s official website. The statement read: “Real Madrid CF and RCD Mallorca have agreed to the transfer of Takefusa Kubo for this season, until June 30, 2020.” DAILY POST had reported that Kubo joined Real Madrid in the summer transfer window. The Japanese star was signed after the Los Blancos unveiled Eden Hazard. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.